WEBVTT

00:00.633 --> 00:03.235
<i>Joining us now,</i>
<i>the reporter</i>

00:03.237 --> 00:04.503
<i>Who broke this story--</i>
<i>vanessa chandler</i>

00:04.505 --> 00:06.105
Of the "post's" styles section.

00:06.107 --> 00:09.041
<i>Former white house</i>
<i>communications director</i>

00:09.043 --> 00:10.642
<i>Olivia pope.</i>

00:10.644 --> 00:12.644
<i>How sure are you</i>
<i>that she's the woman</i>

00:12.646 --> 00:15.180
<i>Who had an alleged affair</i>
<i>with president grant?</i>

00:15.182 --> 00:17.149
<i>It's just one source,</i>
<i>but it's a good source--</i>

00:17.151 --> 00:19.385
<i>A source in a position</i>
<i>to know the true identity</i>

00:19.387 --> 00:21.186
<i>Of the president's mistress.</i>
<i>(clicks)</i>

00:21.188 --> 00:26.025
<i>Come out of the woodwork</i>
<i>and more details emerge.</i>

00:26.027 --> 00:28.027
<i>Can you give us an idea</i>
<i>of how high up</i>

00:28.029 --> 00:33.098
<i>No, but I will say that</i>
<i>my source is 100% sure...</i>
<i>(lock clicks)</i>

00:33.100 --> 00:34.700
<i>That ms. Pope is</i>
<i>the president's mistress,</i>

00:34.702 --> 00:36.101
<i>And if they're right--</i>

00:36.103 --> 00:37.736
<i>And obviously I believe</i>
<i>they are--</i>

00:37.738 --> 00:40.139
<i>It's only a matter of time</i>
<i>before more details come out.</i>

00:46.179 --> 00:48.213
22 minutes
without making a sound.

00:48.215 --> 00:51.150
If only you'd been
this quiet as a child.

00:52.152 --> 00:54.119
Why did you try
to have me killed?

00:54.121 --> 00:55.421
I didn't try
to have you killed.

00:55.423 --> 00:58.490
I tried to have
jake ballard killed.

00:58.492 --> 01:00.726
Hmm. We're here.

01:07.834 --> 01:11.136
No.
You've gotten yourself into
a bit of trouble, olivia,

01:11.138 --> 01:14.073
And I'm here to fix it.
No.

01:14.075 --> 01:15.808
Now listen to me.
You raised your skirt

01:15.810 --> 01:18.210
And opened your knees
and gave it away

01:18.212 --> 01:19.745
To a man
with too much power.

01:19.747 --> 01:21.847
You're not rare.
You're not special.

01:21.849 --> 01:23.849
Your story's no different
than a thousand other stories

01:23.851 --> 01:25.684
In this town,
so you know how this goes.

01:25.686 --> 01:29.555
First they'll smile, be warm,
sympathetic, on your side,

01:29.557 --> 01:31.390
Letting you know that
they will fight for you.

01:31.392 --> 01:34.560
They will lull you into
a false sense of security.

01:34.562 --> 01:37.563
And then, once your belly
is exposed,

01:37.565 --> 01:40.599
They will gut you
and everyone you know.

01:40.601 --> 01:44.203
And by the time you realize
you should be fighting back,

01:44.205 --> 01:46.839
Well, you're already
bleeding to death.

01:46.841 --> 01:50.442
<i>That</i> is the presidency
versus you.

01:50.444 --> 01:52.778
Whose victory do you think
they will fight for?

01:52.780 --> 01:55.114
Whose body do you think
they will bury?

01:55.116 --> 01:57.416
He would never--
"he would never."

01:57.418 --> 02:00.652
You and I both know
that he is <i>not</i> in charge.

02:00.654 --> 02:03.188
He is <i>never</i> in charge.

02:03.190 --> 02:04.823
Power is in charge.

02:04.825 --> 02:07.726
Power got him elected.

02:07.728 --> 02:10.729
I know more than you could
possibly imagine

02:10.731 --> 02:14.466
About things of which
you cannot dream.

02:14.468 --> 02:19.238
He told you that you
would be first lady,

02:19.240 --> 02:21.340
And    <i>y</i>believed him!

02:21.342 --> 02:24.343
Did I not raise you
for better?

02:24.345 --> 02:26.912
How many times have I told you
you have to be...

02:26.914 --> 02:29.148
What?

02:30.817 --> 02:35.821
You have to be...
What?

02:35.823 --> 02:36.855
Twice...

02:36.857 --> 02:39.391
<i>What?!</i>

02:39.393 --> 02:41.693
(voice breaks)
twice as good.

02:41.695 --> 02:43.462
Twice as good as them

02:43.464 --> 02:46.498
To get <i>half</i>
<i>of what they have.</i>

02:46.500 --> 02:49.334
Sleeping with that...
(sighs)

02:49.336 --> 02:52.404
For god sakes!

02:52.406 --> 02:55.307
You know to aim higher.

02:55.309 --> 02:57.309
At the very least,
you could have aimed for

02:57.311 --> 02:59.244
Chief of staff,
secretary of state!

02:59.246 --> 03:01.880
First lady!

03:04.450 --> 03:06.919
Do you have to be
so mediocre?

03:21.501 --> 03:23.402
Your staff will be
taken care of financially.

03:23.404 --> 03:25.904
Your business will continue
to run.

03:25.906 --> 03:27.873
Money is not a problem.
There's always money.

03:27.875 --> 03:30.275
Money bought that plane.
Money bought the silence

03:30.277 --> 03:32.311
Of the gentleman
who will fly that plane.

03:32.313 --> 03:34.880
On board, you will
find an envelope.

03:34.882 --> 03:37.482
It contains a passport,
a swiss bank book,

03:37.484 --> 03:40.352
A go file,
an entirely new identity.

03:40.354 --> 03:42.588
There is a very nice island
waiting for you

03:42.590 --> 03:43.922
At the end of the flight.

03:43.924 --> 03:46.358
You will stay there
for eight months.

03:46.360 --> 03:49.294
Then I can arrange
a place for you in brussels.

03:49.296 --> 03:51.797
Thailand, if you prefer,
johannesburg--

03:51.799 --> 03:54.933
Anyplace but here, really,
as long as you disappear.

03:54.935 --> 03:56.702
And what if I don't want
to go?

03:56.704 --> 03:58.737
Olivia, you're getting
on that plane

03:58.739 --> 04:00.505
Come hell or high water.

04:00.507 --> 04:03.675
And to be clear,
<i>I</i> am the hell

04:03.677 --> 04:05.978
<i>And</i> the high water.

04:07.547 --> 04:13.318
(projector and camera shutter
clicking)

04:13.320 --> 04:17.256
(airplane engines whirring)

04:17.258 --> 04:19.291
We'll be taking off in a moment.
Can I get you anything to drink?

04:19.293 --> 04:21.326
No. Thank you.

04:21.328 --> 04:24.029
Can I...
Borrow your phone?

04:26.833 --> 04:28.000
(sighs) where are you?

04:28.002 --> 04:29.935
I'm sitting in a jet
on a runway.

04:29.937 --> 04:32.037
Where are you going?
Nowhere. I'm disappearing.

04:32.039 --> 04:35.307
That is not an option.
It is. Apparently,
it's very simple.

04:35.309 --> 04:39.478
I just get on this plane
and I disappear into thin air.

04:42.715 --> 04:45.317
Get off the plane.
Don't run.

04:45.319 --> 04:47.986
You need me here so you can
throw me under the bus?

04:47.988 --> 04:50.689
I know how this goes. I can
run this play in my sleep.

04:50.691 --> 04:53.325
You'll burn me.
I won't burn you.

04:53.327 --> 04:55.894
Not unless you burn me.
We are on the same side.
Are we?

04:55.896 --> 04:57.029
Who leaked my name, cy?

04:57.031 --> 04:58.997
When I find out,
they will suffer.

04:58.999 --> 05:00.465
Get off the plane!

05:00.467 --> 05:01.967
I just wanted to say good-bye.
Olivia--

05:01.969 --> 05:04.703
Tell him I said good-bye.
Olivia. Olivia!

05:04.705 --> 05:05.971
What?

05:05.973 --> 05:09.908
If you... Disappear--
if you <i>disappear,</i>

05:09.910 --> 05:11.910
He will think
that I had you killed.

05:11.912 --> 05:13.612
And he will never trust me
again.

05:13.614 --> 05:14.913
He barely trusts me
as it is,

05:14.915 --> 05:17.649
And I will not be able
to help him out of this.

05:17.651 --> 05:20.085
If he thinks you're dead,
I won't be able to save him.

05:21.854 --> 05:23.922
Don't run!
I have done dark things,

05:23.924 --> 05:26.091
But I have also been your friend
and your champion.

05:26.093 --> 05:28.026
When you aren't a monster?

05:28.028 --> 05:30.996
I am a monster, but, honey,
I'm your monster!

05:30.998 --> 05:32.764
And I will fix this.

05:32.766 --> 05:34.900
I will put this ridiculous,
untrue rumor

05:34.902 --> 05:37.769
About you having an affair
with the president to rest.

05:37.771 --> 05:39.905
I will put it down.
I will bury it!

05:39.907 --> 05:41.440
I just need a little time,

05:41.442 --> 05:44.676
And I just need you
not to run.

05:44.678 --> 05:46.011
(breathing heavily)

05:46.013 --> 05:48.447
I need you to get off
the plane, my friend.

05:48.449 --> 05:50.682
Get off the plane.

05:57.890 --> 05:59.691
Olivia!
I'm not going.

05:59.693 --> 06:00.992
Yes, you are.

06:00.994 --> 06:02.761
Thanks for the offer, but no.

06:02.763 --> 06:06.064
I am many things.
Stupid is not one of them.

06:06.066 --> 06:09.000
Olivia, you can't possibly think
you're going to return

06:09.002 --> 06:11.970
To your old life
as if nothing is happening.

06:11.972 --> 06:15.774
What is happening is that I am
taking care of myself!

06:15.776 --> 06:18.510
Take me to my office.

06:20.113 --> 06:22.147
The white house
will destroy you.

06:22.149 --> 06:25.817
That's what mom used to
tell me about you.

06:25.819 --> 06:27.853
(window whirs)

06:32.992 --> 06:36.895
Like I said and will continue
to say in a variety of ways,

06:36.897 --> 06:40.432
The white house has no official
comment on these accusations

06:40.434 --> 06:43.568
And no plans to comment further.
(reporters shouting questions)

06:43.570 --> 06:44.870
You want the vice president

06:44.872 --> 06:46.738
To take on the president's
public appearances

06:46.740 --> 06:48.573
In the middle of all this?
Th-that--

06:48.575 --> 06:50.041
Until I can find the source
of the fire and put it out,

06:50.043 --> 06:53.845
She's gonna get the questions.
<i>All</i> the questions.

06:53.847 --> 06:55.981
Then she'll dodge them
and be very good at it.

06:55.983 --> 06:58.116
Cyrus, maybe you and I should
get together and discuss this.
I don't think so.

06:58.118 --> 07:01.086
Ma'am!
No, I will not be
aiding and abetting a man

07:01.088 --> 07:03.121
Breaking his marriage vows
and laying with another woman.

07:03.123 --> 07:05.924
I will not be surrendering
that piece of my soul.

07:05.926 --> 07:07.759
I am the lord's witness.

07:07.761 --> 07:10.662
No...

07:10.664 --> 07:12.664
No! The people.

07:12.666 --> 07:15.667
The people,
madame vice president...

07:15.669 --> 07:18.670
(chuckles) the people
elected you

07:18.672 --> 07:21.606
To be the president's sidekick,
not the lord!

07:21.608 --> 07:24.109
The lord did not fill out
his voter registration card.

07:24.111 --> 07:27.546
So guess what. The lord
does not have the right to vote

07:27.548 --> 07:29.548
In the United States
of america!

07:29.550 --> 07:31.550
I am done with you
and your superiority

07:31.552 --> 07:32.851
And your rudeness.

07:32.853 --> 07:35.687
I have never once mentioned
how I feel about

07:35.689 --> 07:37.756
Your godless homosexual
lifestyle

07:37.758 --> 07:40.792
And that poor, sweet
brown baby

07:40.794 --> 07:42.861
That you have dragged
into it.

07:42.863 --> 07:44.996
I keep my personal opinions
to myself.

07:44.998 --> 07:49.167
But you find any opportunity
each and every day to belittle

07:49.169 --> 07:51.536
Me and my desire
to serve the lord.

07:51.538 --> 07:53.905
You have no respect.
Not for me, not for the voters

07:53.907 --> 07:56.675
I handed you on a platter
the last election,

07:56.677 --> 07:58.844
The voters I will take with me
when I go.

07:58.846 --> 08:01.580
Go? Wh-where are you going!?
Canada?

08:01.582 --> 08:03.915
Because that's the only place
you have a chance

08:03.917 --> 08:06.051
Of being elected
on a sitting president

08:06.053 --> 08:08.587
From your own party, who--

08:08.589 --> 08:10.922
Who is sleeping with whores!
I'd like to speak
with sally alone, please.

08:12.158 --> 08:13.925
Alone.
(sally sighs)

08:13.927 --> 08:15.060
Please.

08:15.062 --> 08:16.728
(whispers) okay.

08:16.730 --> 08:20.532
Okay.
(sighs)

08:20.534 --> 08:22.100
(door opens)

08:24.704 --> 08:26.838
(inhales and sighs)

08:28.875 --> 08:30.775
Well?

08:30.777 --> 08:33.778
Do you drink ever?
Excuse me?

08:33.780 --> 08:35.647
I'm not trying to just...

08:35.649 --> 08:37.716
If you were a man,
I'd offer you a scotch.

08:37.718 --> 08:39.684
And I thought, I'm kind of
an ass if I only offer you

08:39.686 --> 08:41.553
The scotch if you're a man.

08:41.555 --> 08:43.154
What is that? Some
prep school crap I learned.

08:43.156 --> 08:45.257
Uh... Anyway,

08:45.259 --> 08:47.125
Do you... Drink?

08:47.127 --> 08:49.694
(inhales sharply)

08:49.696 --> 08:52.597
I would like a scotch.
Neat.

08:55.801 --> 08:57.702
Sally... (exhales)

08:57.704 --> 08:58.837
Yes?

08:58.839 --> 09:01.706
(pours liquor, bottle clatters)

09:01.708 --> 09:05.777
I slept with someone
who is not my wife.

09:08.047 --> 09:10.649
You're not surprised
that I cheated.

09:10.651 --> 09:11.917
You're surprised
that I'm admitting it.

09:11.919 --> 09:14.052
(pours liquor)
which is...

09:14.054 --> 09:17.622
(bottle clatters)
I did. I had an affair.

09:17.624 --> 09:21.593
I take responsibility,
and I'm sorry.

09:22.862 --> 09:23.995
I failed you.

09:23.997 --> 09:25.797
Me, sir?

09:25.799 --> 09:28.199
You. As your team member,
as your president,

09:28.201 --> 09:31.036
As your fellow citizen.

09:31.038 --> 09:34.072
I did not live up to my promise
to be the best man I could be.

09:34.074 --> 09:35.907
I lied.

09:35.909 --> 09:38.777
I lived a lie.

09:38.779 --> 09:40.912
And I am sorry about that.

09:42.748 --> 09:43.848
Okay?

09:45.585 --> 09:46.918
All right, mr. President.

09:46.920 --> 09:49.120
Okay.

09:49.122 --> 09:51.590
So...

09:51.592 --> 09:53.758
These public appearances
cyrus is asking you

09:53.760 --> 09:55.226
To stand in on for me...
Sir?

09:55.228 --> 09:58.863
Sally, it's time for me
to do the right thing.

09:58.865 --> 10:01.733
Be the leader I've always
wanted to be.

10:01.735 --> 10:04.603
In order to do so, I have to
stand in front of the world

10:04.605 --> 10:06.071
And say who I am
and what I've done

10:06.073 --> 10:07.739
And deal
with the consequences,

10:07.741 --> 10:11.009
That moment is coming,
and I want it to come.

10:11.011 --> 10:13.612
What I'm asking you

10:13.614 --> 10:17.248
Is for the chance
to buy a little time

10:17.250 --> 10:20.752
To get the people in my life
ready for that moment.

10:22.888 --> 10:24.656
Can you do that for me?

10:25.992 --> 10:29.361
(inhales)

10:29.363 --> 10:31.363
Yes. (exhales)

10:31.365 --> 10:32.797
Yes, I can.

10:34.800 --> 10:36.968
(projector and camera shutter
clicking)

10:36.970 --> 10:40.805
(man) there she is!

10:40.807 --> 10:44.342
(reporters shouting questions,
camera shutters clicking)

10:44.344 --> 10:46.177
(pounding on limousine)

10:46.179 --> 10:50.248
(clamoring)

10:50.250 --> 10:52.751
(man) move out of the way!

10:52.753 --> 10:55.086
Get off the car!
Don't!

10:55.088 --> 10:56.755
Move out of the way!

10:56.757 --> 10:58.723
Hey. Hey!

10:58.725 --> 11:01.359
(camera shutter clicking)

11:01.361 --> 11:04.763
(clamoring continues)

11:04.765 --> 11:07.365
Olivia! Take my hand.

11:07.367 --> 11:11.269
(all shouting at once)

11:11.271 --> 11:12.937
(projector and camera shutter
clicking)

11:12.939 --> 11:15.106
(shouting continues)

11:15.108 --> 11:16.708
(projector and camera shutter
clicking)

11:18.878 --> 11:20.812
(abby) what should we do?
What's our first move?

11:20.814 --> 11:22.847
We do nothing.
It's being handled,

11:22.849 --> 11:24.249
Which means all of you can
go back to work,

11:24.251 --> 11:25.950
Business as usual.
Business as usual?

11:25.952 --> 11:27.285
How is that even possible?

11:27.287 --> 11:29.354
You pick up the phone
and call our clients.

11:29.356 --> 11:32.323
Show them we're as dedicated
to them as ever.

11:32.325 --> 11:34.392
<i>What?</i>
<i>Are we really not gonna</i>
<i>talking about</i>

11:34.394 --> 11:37.062
The fact that you're the most
infamous woman in america...
The world.

11:37.064 --> 11:38.730
In the <i>world</i> right now?!

11:38.732 --> 11:42.000
It's being handled.
By who? The white house?

11:42.002 --> 11:44.002
Liv, the phone has been ringing
off the hook all morning.

11:44.004 --> 11:46.237
Aside from the reporters,
the only people getting through

11:46.239 --> 11:47.872
Are clients calling to fire us.

11:50.276 --> 11:52.744
It's olivia pope
for governor suarez.

11:52.746 --> 11:55.046
Yes, that olivia pope.

11:55.048 --> 11:57.982
The white house is going
to bury her!

11:57.984 --> 11:59.484
Okay, jeff, your call,
but don't call me in two hours

11:59.486 --> 12:01.252
When this nonsense blows over.

12:01.254 --> 12:04.389
And you know who goes down
with her? Us. We all burn.

12:04.391 --> 12:06.057
You know it, I know it,
everybody knows it.

12:06.059 --> 12:08.193
Ambassador heller,
<i>guten tag.</i>

12:08.195 --> 12:09.828
There is no one else on earth

12:09.830 --> 12:11.496
Who can handle something
like this better than we can.

12:11.498 --> 12:13.064
(pounds desk)
so that's what we do.

12:13.066 --> 12:14.866
Senator, I understand
you're in a tough position.

12:14.868 --> 12:16.401
I do, but honestly, so was I

12:16.403 --> 12:18.203
When I defended your son
who was guilty of rape.

12:18.205 --> 12:20.138
I never once left your side,
and--

12:20.140 --> 12:22.841
We handle it.

12:22.843 --> 12:24.809
Even if liv won't.

12:26.045 --> 12:28.313
(voice breaks) I understand.

12:30.082 --> 12:32.016
Good-bye, sandra.

12:32.018 --> 12:33.818
(sets down phone)
(exhales)

12:33.820 --> 12:36.421
(projector and camera shutter
clicking)

12:39.158 --> 12:41.192
Hello, sweetheart.

12:41.194 --> 12:42.527
You want something.

12:42.529 --> 12:45.163
Shame to get scooped
by a society page blogger.

12:45.165 --> 12:46.531
She's so beneath you.

12:46.533 --> 12:48.867
How does someone
that low-level get access

12:48.869 --> 12:50.001
To white house sources?

12:50.003 --> 12:51.803
Is she making it up
just to get ahead

12:51.805 --> 12:53.805
Or sleeping with someone...
No.

12:53.807 --> 12:55.240
You know, we're not
playing this game.

12:55.242 --> 12:56.808
I'm playing,
and if you play, too,

12:56.810 --> 12:58.042
You get a prize, a scoop.

12:58.044 --> 12:59.244
A scoop?

12:59.246 --> 13:00.411
A good one.

13:03.849 --> 13:05.850
Malloy's.
Excuse me?

13:05.852 --> 13:07.418
Bottom feeders like vanessa
tend to troll

13:07.420 --> 13:09.788
For crumbs of gossip
at malloy's.

13:09.790 --> 13:10.555
What's special
about malloy's?

13:10.557 --> 13:13.358
Secret service
drinks there.

13:16.829 --> 13:18.163
Sweetheart!

13:18.165 --> 13:20.465
You owe me!

13:35.881 --> 13:38.082
Hal.
Ma'am.

13:38.084 --> 13:40.852
I need to ask you
a question, hal,

13:40.854 --> 13:42.854
And I would like you
to be honest with me.

13:42.856 --> 13:46.157
About olivia pope
and my husband got started?

13:46.159 --> 13:47.458
(sighs)

13:47.460 --> 13:49.394
I only ask because I know
that sometimes

13:49.396 --> 13:51.229
You and the other agents
like to drink at malloy's

13:51.231 --> 13:53.865
After work, and there's
always journalists there

13:53.867 --> 13:56.935
Waiting around to pick up
